File: Lab technicians gather around a machine as they test samples for COVID-19. JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize announced on Tuesday the department has recorded another death in Parklands, KwaZulu-Natal bringing the death toll to 13. The man had previously reported prostate cancer as an underlying condition. READ: COVID-19: SA death toll at 12 The department conveyed its condolences to the family of the deceased. The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases is now 1,749. The minister expressed concern about the rise of infections at the St Augustine's Hospital in Durban. READ: Denosa calls for greater protection of nurses In total, 66 people at the hospital have tested positive over the past few days. About 48 of them are staff. The KZN Department of Health is engaging the hospital with a view to closing parts of the hospital down. READ: Netcare denies COVID-19 positve doc was allowed back to work "We hope the fumigation process will start soon there. We have also assigned specialists there. "We must always be on the lookout. The infection can seep in from any institution. We must now trace all the contacts. It is a matter of serious concern and we are dealing with it," the minister said. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.